4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT CREATING THE MONTANA WATER DEVELOPMENT STATE
5 SPECIAL REVENUE ACCOUNT; ALLOWING FOR AUTHORIZED EXPENDITURES RELATED TO WATER
6 DEVELOPMENTS; PROVIDING FOR FUND TRANSFERS; AMENDING SECTIONS 15-38-302 AND 85-1-631,
7 MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Montana water development state special revenue account. (1) (a)
12 There is a Montana water development state special revenue fund as provided for in 17-2-102.
13 (b) The fund retains its own interest.
14 (c) The account is composed of revenue gifted to the state or transferred to the account by the
15 legislature and interest generated by the account.
16 (2) Ninety percent of the earnings from the investment must be distributed to the water storage
17 state special revenue account established in 85-1-631. Ten percent of the earnings from the investment must
18 be distributed to the natural resources projects state special revenue account established in 15-38-302 to be
19 used for water storage pilot projects and dam inspections required under 85-15-213.
20
21 Section 2. Section 15-38-302, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "15-38-302. Natural resources projects state special revenue account created -- revenue
23 allocated -- limitations on appropriations from account. (1) There is a natural resources projects state
24 special revenue account within the state special revenue fund established in 17-2-102.
25 (2) There must be paid into the natural resources projects state special revenue account money
26 allocated from:
27 (a) the interest income of the resource indemnity trust fund under the provisions of 15-38-202;
28 (b) the resource indemnity and ground water assessment tax under the provisions of 15-38-106;
