11 Section 3. Section 85-1-631, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "85-1-631. Water storage state special revenue account created -- revenues allocated --
13 appropriations from account. (1) There is a water storage state special revenue account within the state
14 special revenue fund established in 17-2-102.
15 (2) There must be paid into the water storage state special revenue account:
16 (a) for the biennium beginning July 1, 2007, the proceeds of the resource indemnity and ground
17 water assessment tax as provided in 15-38-106; and
18 (b) money allocated from the resource indemnity trust fund interest earnings pursuant to 15-38-202
19 and all revenue of the works and other money as provided in 85-1-332. ; and
20 (c) ninety percent of the interest earned from the Montana water development state special
21 revenue account established in [section 1].
22 (3) All revenue provided from 85-1-332(1)(e) and (1)(f) deposited in the water storage state special
23 revenue account must be appropriated solely for the construction, operation, rehabilitation, expansion,
24 maintenance, and modification of state-owned water storage projects.
25 (4) Money that was not encumbered or expended from the water storage state special revenue
26 account during the previous biennium must remain in the account.
27 (5) Deposits to the water storage state special revenue account must be placed in short-term
28 investments and accrue interest, which must be deposited in the water storage state special revenue account.
